{"slug": "forced_liquidation", "name": "Forced Liquidation", "commander": "Kefka, Court Mage", "colors": "Grixis", "pips": ["U", "B", "R"], "archetype": "Wheel-burn / punisher static", "status": "**Cards on order**", "bracket": 3, "score": 16, "axes": [{"label": "Core loop", "score": 5}, {"label": "Kill reliability", "score": 4}, {"label": "Durability", "score": 3}, {"label": "Interaction", "score": 4}], "axesTotal": "16/20", "gc": ["Notion Thief", "Demonic Tutor", "Mana Vault"], "kicker": "In the Grixis corner", "corner": "Bracket 3 \u00b7 Grixis", "tagline": "Notion Thief + Psychosis Crawler + any wheel -> one-wheel table kill (statics fire through Grand Abolisher)", "colorLine": "Grixis \u00b7 UBR", "idea": "This deck weaponizes drawing cards as a damage source.", "vitals": [{"label": "Clock", "value": "T9", "accent": true, "sub": "decap T8"}, {"label": "Decap", "value": "T8", "sub": "one opponent"}, {"label": "Game Changers", "value": "3/3", "sub": "bracket-3 cap"}], "briefKillsCaption": "the lines that win", "briefKills": [{"idx": "01", "tag": "table", "primary": true, "clock": "table T9", "line": "Notion Thief + Psychosis Crawler + any wheel (Niv-Mizzet, Parun = redundant version) \u2192 you draw ~28 (your 7 + ~21 redirected) \u2192 each opponent loses ~28 AND draws nothing"}, {"idx": "02", "tag": "table", "primary": false, "clock": "table T9", "line": "2+ opponent-draw punishers (Underworld Dreams / Fate Unraveler / Sheoldred / Ob Nixilis) + a wheel \u00b7 Bloodletter of Aclazotz doubles it \u2192 each opponent draws 7 \u2192 ~14\u201328 life loss each (lethal-or-bust \u2014 never spin on one)"}], "openings": ["Weakest axis \u2014 Durability (3/5): the judges' soft spot.", "Lethal-or-bust: never wheel on <2 punishers; Kitten+Channeler backup combo is resilience not speed.", "Decap never-closes in 4% of goldfish games \u2014 a grind risk.", "Tables (all three) never-close 11% of the time."], "clock": {"decap": "T8", "table": "T9", "grid": [4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12], "decapCurve": [1, 5, 15, 34, 56, 74, 86, 96], "tableCurve": [0, 3, 9, 21, 40, 59, 73, 89], "never": [4, 11], "src": "lab kfk_clock_lab @40k 2026-06-28", "sub": "measured kill-clock", "headline": [{"label": "Decap \u00b7 one opp", "value": "T8", "sub": "median kill", "kind": "decap"}, {"label": "Table \u00b7 all three", "value": "T9", "sub": "median kill", "kind": "table"}], "bands": [{"label": "decap", "from": 8, "to": 8, "kind": "decap"}, {"label": "table", "from": 9, "to": 9, "kind": "table"}], "ticks": [4, 6, 8, 10, 12], "axisFrom": 4, "axisTo": 12, "note": "", "noteLabel": "", "caption": "Decap (one opponent) lands around T8; the full table around T9."}, "gamePlan": "This deck weaponizes *drawing cards* as a damage source. The shell is ~7 wheel effects (Windfall, Echo of Eons, Reforge the Soul, Magus of the Wheel, Jace's Archivist, Molten Psyche, Dark Deal) plus Peer into the Abyss, backed by a redundant suite of static punishers that convert every draw or discard into life loss. Because the kill is a *wheel resolved on your own turn* feeding *static* triggers \u2014 not casts or activated abilities \u2014 it fires straight through a Grand Abolisher lock, which is the entire reason this deck exists (it answers the pod's recurring T6\u20137 Abolisher combo archenemy that the counter-heavy decks can't). Kefka himself is the value/disruption engine and a deliberate removal-magnet, **not** a combo linchpin: his ETB (each player discards, you draw one per card *type* discarded) is guaranteed value per cast, and the win runs entirely from the command zone if he dies.", "winLine": "Notion Thief + Psychosis Crawler + any wheel -> one-wheel table kill (statics fire through Grand Abolisher)", "finishers": [{"name": "Notion Thief + Psychosis Crawler + any wheel", "tag": "marquee, near-deterministic", "note": "Notion Thief redirects every opponent's wheel-draws to you; Psychosis Crawler pings each opponent 1 per *your* draw."}, {"name": "Multi-punisher wheel", "tag": "the default burn", "note": "with 2+ opponent-draw punishers down (Underworld Dreams, Fate Unraveler, Kederekt Parasite, Ob Nixilis the Hate-Twisted, Sheoldred), one wheel makes each opponent draw 7 \u2192 ~14\u201328 damage/life-loss each."}, {"name": "Peer into the Abyss", "tag": "single-target nuke", "note": "pointed at one opponent with a draw-punisher out: they draw ~half their library (\u2192 that much damage) and lose half their life."}, {"name": "Displacer Kitten + Aether Channeler + Sol Ring + Mana Vault", "tag": "backup combo \u2014 resilience, not speed", "note": "CSB-registered complete combo `1170-1393-2364-5034`: infinite ETB + infinite colorless mana; route Channeler's \"draw a card\" ETB each iteration into Niv-Mizzet (1 dmg/draw) or Psychosis Crawler (each opp \u22121/draw) for a lethal that's commander-independent and resolves on your turn."}], "rulings": [{"name": "Notion Thief is a replacement, not a trigger", "note": "it uses no stack and can't be countered. It redirects to you every opponent draw except the first one in each of their draw steps; wheel draws aren't draw-step draws, so all of them are stolen. Flash it in before the wheel resolves."}, {"name": "Notion Thief turns OFF your opponent-draw punishers", "note": "while it's out, opponents don't draw (you do), so Underworld Dreams / Fate Unraveler won't fire on a wheel. Psychosis Crawler carries that kill instead. Don't plan on both at once."}, {"name": "Psychosis Crawler counts YOUR draws", "note": "each opponent loses 1 life per card you draw, once per card (its ruling: multiple draws \u2192 multiple triggers). Notion Thief + a 7-card wheel = ~7 per opponent stolen onto you = a ~21 table swing. The marquee line."}, {"name": "Kefka draws per card TYPE, not per card", "note": "each player discards one card; you draw one card for each distinct type among them (three lands \u2192 1 draw; land + instant + creature \u2192 3). And those are your draws, so they ping through Psychosis Crawler."}, {"name": "Peer into the Abyss rounds UP both halves", "note": "aimed at an opponent with the draw-punishers out, they ping themselves drawing half their library; aimed at an opponent under your Notion Thief, you draw their half-library (Crawler hammers the table) and they still lose half their life. It only refuels that one player, never the table."}, {"name": "Underworld Dreams / Fate Unraveler ping per card and only on OPPONENTS' draws", "note": "a \"put into hand\" that doesn't use the word draw (a tutor) doesn't ping; a wheel or Peer does."}, {"name": "The wheel-kill resolves THROUGH a Grand Abolisher", "note": "it's a sorcery cast on your turn feeding static triggers, with no targeting of opponents' permanents and no stack interaction with their combo, so their Abolisher (which only locks you out on their turn) can't stop it. The entire reason this deck exists."}, {"name": "Displacer Kitten triggers on NONCREATURE spells only", "note": "the backup combo (Kitten + Aether Channeler + Sol Ring + Mana Vault) blinks a rock for net mana and Channeler for a draw each cast. Don't blink a token (it vanishes), and remember the blink strips counters and auras."}], "composition": [{"name": "Wheels & Mass Draw", "count": 8, "win": false}, {"name": "Draw Punishers", "count": 8, "win": false}, {"name": "Discard Punishers & Amplifiers", "count": 6, "win": false}, {"name": "Backup Combo (Displacer Kitten line)", "count": 2, "win": true}, {"name": "Tutors", "count": 3, "win": false}, {"name": "Card Filtering & Recursion", "count": 6, "win": false}, {"name": "Removal", "count": 8, "win": false}, {"name": "Counters", "count": 6, "win": false}, {"name": "Protection & Static", "count": 4, "win": false}, {"name": "Mana Rocks & Rituals", "count": 12, "win": false}, {"name": "Lands", "count": 36, "win": false}], "decklist": {"total": 100, "grouped": true, "commander": {"n": "Kefka, Court Mage", "gc": false}, "groups": [{"name": "Wheels & Mass Draw", "count": 8, "cards": [{"n": "Dark Deal", "gc": false}, {"n": "Echo of Eons", "gc": false}, {"n": "Jace's Archivist", "gc": false}, {"n": "Magus of the Wheel", "gc": false}, {"n": "Molten Psyche", "gc": false}, {"n": "Peer into the Abyss", "gc": false}, {"n": "Reforge the Soul", "gc": false}, {"n": "Windfall", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Draw Punishers", "count": 8, "cards": [{"n": "Fate Unraveler", "gc": false}, {"n": "Kederekt Parasite", "gc": false}, {"n": "Niv-Mizzet, Parun", "gc": false}, {"n": "Notion Thief", "gc": true}, {"n": "Ob Nixilis, the Hate-Twisted", "gc": false}, {"n": "Psychosis Crawler", "gc": false}, {"n": "Sheoldred, the Apocalypse", "gc": false}, {"n": "Underworld Dreams", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Discard Punishers & Amplifiers", "count": 6, "cards": [{"n": "Bloodletter of Aclazotz", "gc": false}, {"n": "Glint-Horn Buccaneer", "gc": false}, {"n": "Liliana's Caress", "gc": false}, {"n": "Megrim", "gc": false}, {"n": "Nicol Bolas, the Ravager", "gc": false}, {"n": "Waste Not", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Backup Combo", "count": 2, "cards": [{"n": "Aether Channeler", "gc": false}, {"n": "Displacer Kitten", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Tutors", "count": 3, "cards": [{"n": "Demonic Tutor", "gc": true}, {"n": "Final Parting", "gc": false}, {"n": "Grim Tutor", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Card Filtering & Recursion", "count": 6, "cards": [{"n": "Faithless Looting", "gc": false}, {"n": "Frantic Search", "gc": false}, {"n": "Past in Flames", "gc": false}, {"n": "Ponder", "gc": false}, {"n": "Preordain", "gc": false}, {"n": "Thrill of Possibility", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Removal", "count": 8, "cards": [{"n": "Blasphemous Act", "gc": false}, {"n": "Bloodchief's Thirst", "gc": false}, {"n": "Chaos Warp", "gc": false}, {"n": "Dismember", "gc": false}, {"n": "Go for the Throat", "gc": false}, {"n": "Heartless Act", "gc": false}, {"n": "Rakdos Charm", "gc": false}, {"n": "Soul Shatter", "gc": false}]}, {"name": "Counters", "count": 6, "cards": [{"n": "An Offer You Can't Refuse", "gc": false}, {"n": 